<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 4:12PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southwestern Appomattox and eastern Campbell Counties through 445 PM
EDT...
At 412 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Appomattox, moving southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Appomattox...
Concord...
Rustburg...
Mike...
Appomattox National Historic Park...
Spout Spring...
and Spring Mills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
